The paper discusses the low overlap among search results of academic search engines, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and digital libraries (DL) research. The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing (NLP) techniques to improve search results, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (CL). The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cryptography (CR) and databases (DB) as they deal with information security and storage, respectively.
